<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>LaTeX | MAVENs</title><link>http://localhost:1313/tag/latex/</link><atom:link href="http://localhost:1313/tag/latex/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><description>LaTeX</description><generator>Hugo Blox Builder (https://hugoblox.com)</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Fri, 26 Jan 2024 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><image><url>http://localhost:1313/media/logo.svg</url><title>LaTeX</title><link>http://localhost:1313/tag/latex/</link></image><item><title>mkbib: Bibliography Management Simplified</title><link>http://localhost:1313/software/mkbib/</link><pubDate>Fri, 26 Jan 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>http://localhost:1313/software/mkbib/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="why-mkbib"&gt;Why mkbib?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Managing references is often the most tedious part of research. &lt;strong&gt;mkbib&lt;/strong&gt; automates the heavy lifting, ensuring your citations are clean, consistent, and ready for publication.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id="core-capabilities"&gt;Core Capabilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Automatic Formatting:&lt;/strong&gt; Converts raw metadata into polished BibTeX entries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Duplicate Detection:&lt;/strong&gt; Scans your library to keep your files lean.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CLI-First:&lt;/strong&gt; Designed for speed and integration into automated LaTeX build pipelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3 id="usage"&gt;Usage&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;&lt;span class="c1"&gt;# Example command (adjust based on your actual CLI)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="line"&gt;&lt;span class="cl"&gt;mkbib --input raw_refs.txt --output main.bib
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>